      "status": "doing",
      "title": "Experiment with source hints for failed browser network requests",
      "priority": "low",
      "tags": [
        "agent-browser",
        "network",
        "source-lookup",
        "experiment"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Failed request summaries are useful for QA, but mapping them causally to source files is ambiguous and should be treated as an experiment after network diagnostics are reliable.",
        "The goal is candidate source hints with uncertainty, not definitive blame."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Ensure failed network request summaries include enough safe context: method, URL, status/error, initiator stack if available, and bounded redacted previews.",
        "Prototype optional mapping from request initiator/source maps/local repo search to candidate files and call sites, clearly marking confidence and gaps.",
        "Avoid automatic edits or blame; return evidence and nextActions for manual code inspection.",
        "Evaluate against real local-app failures before deciding whether this belongs in the main tool contract."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "Infer and queue failed-request source lookup experiment from the user's ABN task list.",
